Connecticut Lake Profile Data

Columbia Lake Report

Report Last Updated: August 2024

Columbia Lake is a 271.8 acre lake, located in the town of Columbia within Tolland County, Connecticut. The max measured depth of this lake is 7 meters. It has been sampled by CT DEEP Water Monitoring and Assessment on 4 sampling day(s) between 2012-06-26 and 2014-07-31.

The DEEP Water Monitoring Program conducts ambient monitoring and the related assessments of the States waters, including Connecticuts many lakes and ponds. In Connecticut, there are a total of 2,267 lakes and ponds greater than 10 acres in size.

The Monitoring Program conducts annual monitoring on approximately 10-20 of these lakes and ponds per year. The type and locations of monitoring during a given year is determined by a variety of factors, including participation in regional and national studies, as well as support requests from groups within DEEP.
